<br>
A couple knows by tests that their child will be born with major birth defects, and will have a very short time to live (2-5 years).  They, or adoptive parents should be subjected to the pain of losing that child?  As well, the child will be subjected to intensive hospital stays for his / her entire life.<br>
Where is the quality of life for the child in an antiseptic environenment where he/ she may get held for maybe 2 hours a day tops?  Where is the quality of life for the poor parents?<br>
<br>
A woman due to religious beliefs cannot use birth control, and gets pregnant year after year, until her body wears out and she simply dies in childbirth.  Where is the quality of life for that woman ?   Your argument values the life of a fetus over hers?<br>
<br>
Where is the quality of life for the unborn you so champion?<br>
<br>
Life is precious yes.  But at the cost of the child's contentment / happiness / emotional well being?  In other words - What Life?<br>
<br>
Lets reverse it entirely.  Okies, you are as an adult afflicted with either the diseases of old age, or have an incurable disease (pick one there's a zillion),  which make your life miserable, horrible and unbearable, or were in an accident which made you a brain dead vegetable.  You wish to live this way ?  How is life precious when everything that makes you enjoy life - are gone?<br>
<br>
Quality of life must be greater than the almighty *life is life* arguement.<br>
<br>
